.START 

Health Care Property Investors Inc. said it agreed to finance and build a 60-bed rehabilitation hospital in Colorado Springs for about $10 million. 

The 78,925-square-foot facility will be leased to and operated by Continental Medical Systems Inc., a Mechanicsburg, Pa., health-care company.
Construction is set to be completed by December 1990.
Health Care Property is a real estate investment trust that invests in health-care related facilities. 

